<subSubSection id="C3706566FFE7655FFF1345E6FE59C427" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD536EDFFE7655FFF1345E6FE9BC46F" blockId="35.[151,1439,1117,1501]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
Imago (Fig. 70): Wingspan 
<quantity id="4C929B08FFE7655FFDC345E5FDC5C5F3" box="[535,610,1153,1177]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" unit="mm" value="16.0">16mm</quantity>
. Head and appendages fuscous. Thorax dark fuscous. Forewing dark fuscous irrorate white in irregular manner, but more distinct subterminal broken line; terminal cilia with a fuscous line. Hindwing whitish; inwardly oblique antemedian fascia and outwardly oblique postmedian fascia, fuscous; termen fusous.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD536EDFFE7655FFF134475FE41C443" blockId="35.[151,1439,1117,1501]" box="[199,486,1297,1321]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Male genitalia, unknown.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD536EDFFE7655FFF134451FE59C427" blockId="35.[151,1439,1117,1501]" box="[199,510,1333,1357]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Female genitalia, unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3706566FFE7655FFF13443DFA38C41B" box="[199,1439,1369,1394]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BD536EDFFE7655FFF13443DFA38C41B" blockId="35.[151,1439,1117,1501]" box="[199,1439,1369,1394]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Diagnosis: Distinguished by the lack of any yellow or orange markings, and with no terminal eyespots on the hindwing.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
